Info2: <<
Package: yorick-z
Version: 1.0
Revision: 1
Description: Add-on for the Yorick interpreted language
License: OSI-Approved
Maintainer: Sebastien Maret <bmaret@users.sourceforge.net>
Depends: yorick (>= 1.6), libpng3-shlibs (>=1.2.7), libjpeg-shlibs, libavcodec1-shlibs
BuildDepends: libavcodec1-dev, ffmpeg-dev
Source: http://www.maumae.net/yorick/contrib/yorick-z-%v.tgz
SourceDirectory: yorick-z-%v
Source-MD5: 4c8de258aa4911c4ba38e10864e4035f
SetCFLAGS: -O2
CompileScript: <<
   #!/bin/sh -ev
   export AVCODEC_INC="-I%p/include/ffmpeg"
   export AVCODEC_LIB="-L%p/lib"
   ./configure --ld-avcodec
   make
<<
InstallScript: <<
   install -d %i/share/yorick/1.6/i
   install -d %i/lib/yorick/1.6/i-start
   install -d %i/lib/yorick/1.6/lib
   make Y_HOME=%i/lib/yorick/1.6 Y_SITE=%i/share/yorick/1.6 install
   install -m 644 jpgtest.i mpgtest.i pngtest.i ztest.i check.i %i/share/yorick/1.6/i
<<
DocFiles: README
Homepage: ftp://ftp-icf.llnl.gov/pub/Yorick/doc/index.html  
DescDetail: <<
Yorick-z is a compiled add-on for the Yorick interpreted language.  It
adds support for zlib (the data compression system used by gzip), png
(a lossless image compression format), jpeg (a lossy image compression
format), and mpeg (mpeg1, a compressed video format).
<<
DescUsage: <<
This package include a test program in %p/share/yorick-z/1.6/i.
Type "yorick -batch check.i" in a xterm to run it. Among other
tests, it will create a mpeg file test.mpg that can be open with 
Quicktime.
<<
<<